name: mapbox-vector-tile
summary: mapbox vector tile encoding and decoding.
documentation_summary: The HTML text provides information about the `mapbox-vector-tile` package version 2.0.1, released on January 22, 2023, available on PyPI for encoding and decoding Mapbox Vector Tiles. It requires Python version 3.8 or newer and is compatible with pip installation. The package, licensed under the MIT License, supports various Python versions up to 3.11. It includes detailed instructions for encoding and decoding vector tiles, including handling coordinate transformations and customizing encoding options like quantization and extents. The package also offers a decoding method that returns a string in a specified format and supports using a native protobuf library for improved performance.
